"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-10-france-happy-united-olympics-joy-say-organisers\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS,\\u00a0France\\u00a0(AFP) - Paris Olympics organisers celebrated the country being \\\"united\\\" and \\\"happy\\\" during the widely hailed two-week sports extravaganza amid doubts about how long the feel-good mood will last.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"France has shown itself to the world in a very, very good mindset: confident, united, warm, welcoming,\\\" Head of the Paris 2024 organising committee Tony Estanguet told reporters on the penultimate day of the Games.\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 425, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 211, \"end\": 217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.7167357506013511, \"rank\": 0.3873257434663706, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 327, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.152870975727848e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Estanguet repeatedly voiced his \\\"pride\\\" at organising what he had promised would be an iconic Olympics, which have seen record ticket sales and packed fan zones around the country.\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's an absolutely incredible collective success.\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France has made these Games successful and I am extremely proud,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 734, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.7167357506013511, \"rank\": 0.3873257434663706, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He added: \\\"We have seen a happy France, happy French people, and you should not underestimate that in terms of the legacy of these Games,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 768, \"end\": 774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.7167357506013511, \"rank\": 0.3873257434663706, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 782, \"end\": 795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paralympics will start on August 28 and the former triple gold medal-winning canoeist said he was aware the end of the Olympics and the summer holidays would spell a change in atmosphere.\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 1077, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We will be in a different period, the back-to-work time, the restart of political life,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We will need to adapt to that.\\\"\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French President Emmanuel Macron had called for a \\\"political truce\\\" during the Olympics following inconclusive parliamentary elections that he called on the eve on the Games.\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been largely respected, but the country has been without a permanent government since July and the country's bickering political parties remain sharply divided.\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Estanguet said the weather had been his biggest cause for concern, while the run-up to the start also saw a global information technology outage and an attack on the French railways.\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1723, \"end\": 1729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6166423319596792, \"rank\": 0.5136842549417382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The weather in the final phase was our main difficulty,\\\" said Estanguet.\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heavy rains washed out the opening ceremony on the River Seine - the first times a Games had begun outside the main stadium - while other events had to be postponed because of storms in the first week.\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 2017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1867, \"end\": 1878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was stressed until the very end of this (opening) ceremony,\\\" Estanguet added, saying many parts had to be changed at the last minute.\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not know how the artists were going to adapt.\\\"\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French church leaders and conservatives were left outraged by a scene in the ceremony involving drag queens and lesbian DJ Barbara Butch that appeared to parody Jesus's Last Supper.\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2211, \"end\": 2217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6166423319596792, \"rank\": 0.5136842549417382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2334, \"end\": 2347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}, {\"begin\": 2372, \"end\": 2377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.901417981855598, \"rank\": 0.10524774792145045, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Artistic director Thomas Jolly denied any such intention.\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2412, \"end\": 2418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.7276865411980243, \"rank\": 0.32205221256067745, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He and others involved ended up facing online harassment that led to police complaints.\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2539, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:  HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 2559, \"entities\": []}]}"